WEBVTT

00:39.306 --> 00:41.206
MELISSA:<i> Is there</i>
<i> a world beyond this one?</i>

00:42.710 --> 00:44.343
<i> Do we go there when we die?</i>

00:45.813 --> 00:47.312
<i> Does God exist?</i>

00:48.482 --> 00:49.548
<i> If so,</i>

00:50.484 --> 00:52.317
<i> why do bad things happen?</i>

00:54.789 --> 00:56.956
<i> As children,</i>

00:56.957 --> 00:59.124
<i> we ask these questions</i>
<i> to make sense of the world.</i>

01:00.161 --> 01:02.227
<i> To understand what lies ahead.</i>

01:04.432 --> 01:06.098
<i> But I often wonder,</i>

01:07.101 --> 01:08.667
<i> if we knew the whole truth,</i>

01:09.737 --> 01:11.470
<i> would we be less afraid?</i>

01:13.407 --> 01:14.673
<i> Or more?</i>

01:14.675 --> 01:16.442
(BOY PANTING)

01:31.525 --> 01:33.292
What the fuck?

01:44.138 --> 01:45.337
(GROANS)

01:50.211 --> 01:51.410
(PANTING CONTINUES)

01:59.553 --> 02:01.220
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

02:13.334 --> 02:14.500
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

02:39.927 --> 02:41.360
CHARLENE: Philip?

02:42.863 --> 02:44.363
Philip!

02:46.934 --> 02:49.268
You should blow on it. It's hot.

02:50.738 --> 02:52.771
It's split-pea.
You like split-pea.

02:52.773 --> 02:55.174
No. Ronnie likes split-pea.

02:55.176 --> 02:56.808
(SIGHS) Sorry, Mr. Food Critic.

02:56.810 --> 02:58.777
That's what I made so
that's what you get.

03:00.181 --> 03:01.680
PHILIP: I'll microwave
something later.

03:02.283 --> 03:03.415
(MUSIC PLAYING)

03:08.589 --> 03:10.222
(HAMMERING)

03:15.596 --> 03:16.795
(MUSIC STOPS)

03:18.699 --> 03:19.765
Great.

03:21.402 --> 03:22.534
(SIGHS)

03:22.937 --> 03:24.836
(CAR APPROACHING)

03:39.286 --> 03:40.385
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

03:51.999 --> 03:53.599
Hi, Philip.

03:53.601 --> 03:54.666
Melissa?

03:58.505 --> 04:00.572
I didn't know that you were...

04:02.343 --> 04:03.709
Wow.

04:03.711 --> 04:05.744
Guess it's been a long time.
Yeah.

04:08.282 --> 04:09.982
Is it okay if I come in?

04:11.452 --> 04:13.919
No, yeah, of course. Come on in.

04:17.825 --> 04:19.291
Sit.

04:24.732 --> 04:26.865
Let me clear...
I got it. It's okay.

04:29.503 --> 04:30.602
(EXHALES)

04:36.543 --> 04:38.410
So I heard you've
been living in the city?

04:38.412 --> 04:40.512
Yeah, I was, um,

04:41.382 --> 04:44.716
I am. Just home for a bit.

04:45.519 --> 04:46.718
You know, till the leg heals up.

04:46.720 --> 04:50.022
Yeah, ouch. Are you skiing?

04:50.024 --> 04:51.356
Biking...

04:51.692 --> 04:52.824
...poorly.

04:53.961 --> 04:58.730
Uh, but... Whatever.
You know, it's fine.

05:00.401 --> 05:01.633
Are your parents' home?

05:03.637 --> 05:04.870
Ronnie's Melissa?

05:04.872 --> 05:06.605
It's been five years.
What does she want?

05:06.607 --> 05:07.806
She wants to see you.

05:09.576 --> 05:11.510
She's pregnant.
Oh, great!

05:11.512 --> 05:13.045
The last goddamn
thing I wanna hear

05:13.047 --> 05:15.364
is how goddamn happy she is.

05:15.365 --> 05:17.682
PHILIP: Here's a crazy idea.
Why don't you hear what
she has to say,

05:17.685 --> 05:20.085
before you freak out, okay?

05:27.428 --> 05:29.661
So, you're pregnant?
Yeah.

05:29.663 --> 05:32.030
About 39 weeks, give or take.

05:33.400 --> 05:36.835
Um, I looked for you
at the library, but,

05:36.837 --> 05:39.071
a woman at the front desk
said that you quit.

05:39.073 --> 05:41.740
Oh, I'm sure she did.
Pilla right?

05:41.742 --> 05:43.842
Bad die-job,
tits like torpedoes?

05:45.379 --> 05:46.511
I guess, um,

05:47.748 --> 05:49.381
Mr. Chase isn't around, is he?

05:49.383 --> 05:51.516
No, Mr. Chase is not around.

05:51.518 --> 05:53.585
Mr. Chase has chosen
to become cliche

05:53.587 --> 05:55.654
and live in West Palm Beach
with his new trophy wife.

05:55.656 --> 05:57.489
I know about Florida,
I just didn't...

05:57.491 --> 05:58.757
If you know, then why
would you assume

05:58.759 --> 06:00.392
that man would be in my house?

06:02.930 --> 06:04.529
Are you looking for money?

06:04.531 --> 06:07.566
Jesus, mom!
It's okay. (CHUCKLES)

06:07.568 --> 06:11.770
I know it must seem,
you know, strange,

06:11.772 --> 06:16.408
me showing up here
after all these years,

06:16.410 --> 06:19.544
but I think about
your family everyday.

06:20.481 --> 06:22.414
Especially you, Mrs. Chase.

06:23.117 --> 06:25.050
Losing a child
is the hardest thing

06:25.052 --> 06:26.885
that could every
happen to somebody.

06:27.788 --> 06:28.954
And, um...

06:30.057 --> 06:31.823
I know that
everybody says that...

06:34.528 --> 06:35.961
...that it wasn't my fault.

06:37.598 --> 06:38.797
What happened...

06:39.767 --> 06:41.099
But, um...

06:44.838 --> 06:46.538
Take your time.

06:46.540 --> 06:48.673
Let me just...
Sorry, this isn't coming out

06:48.675 --> 06:50.575
the way I wanted it
to come out, but...

06:53.113 --> 06:56.481
Ronnie used to have
this old stereo in his room.

06:57.618 --> 06:59.184
Do you know if it's still there?

07:01.488 --> 07:02.788
PHILIP: What is this?

07:06.827 --> 07:09.694
I have this one in a 8x10.

07:09.696 --> 07:11.930
You can see how blue
his eyes are in that.

07:20.107 --> 07:22.040
WOMAN OVER TAPE:
<i> I can see</i>
<i> in your eyes...</i>

07:23.110 --> 07:26.011
<i> A loss, longing.</i>

07:26.013 --> 07:29.614
<i> There's a human energy here,</i>

07:29.616 --> 07:32.050
<i> gone before his time.</i>

07:32.052 --> 07:33.618
<i> Someone you love.</i>

07:33.620 --> 07:35.620
<i> Someone who loves</i>
<i> you very much.</i>

07:36.457 --> 07:37.722
MELISSA ON TAPE:<i> Ronnie?</i>

07:38.692 --> 07:40.859
WOMAN ON TAPE:<i> The energy...</i>

07:40.861 --> 07:44.596
<i> There are pictures,</i>
<i> photographs.</i>

07:44.598 --> 07:47.032
MELISSA ON TAPE:<i> His brother,</i>
<i> Philip took a lot of pictures.</i>

07:47.034 --> 07:49.167
<i> I actually think he's a</i>
<i> photographer now.</i>

07:49.169 --> 07:52.204
WOMAN ON TAPE:
<i> He wants his brother</i>
<i> to keep taking pictures.</i>

07:52.206 --> 07:53.972
Are you serious?

07:53.974 --> 07:55.774
Is this what you
came here to tell us,

07:55.776 --> 07:57.742
that Ronnie
liked Philip's pictures?

07:57.744 --> 08:00.245
Do you have any idea what I go
through every single day?

08:00.247 --> 08:02.113
Every time I
walk past this door?

08:02.115 --> 08:05.183
Will you just listen to it?
There's more.

08:12.259 --> 08:15.026
WOMAN ON TAPE:<i> But you're</i>
<i> here about the baby.</i>

08:15.028 --> 08:18.413
<i> First off, it's pure.</i>

08:18.414 --> 08:21.799
<i> Because we give our entire</i>
<i> heart and soul to that person.</i>

08:21.802 --> 08:24.870
<i> He knows your pain</i>
<i> since he passed over.</i>

08:24.872 --> 08:28.240
<i> That's why he's found a way</i>
<i> to carry on in your life.</i>

08:29.209 --> 08:32.511
<i> This baby, it's a part of you.</i>

08:32.513 --> 08:35.647
<i> So, it's a part</i>
<i> of Ronnie as well.</i>

08:44.992 --> 08:46.091
(TAPE STOPS)

08:48.662 --> 08:49.861
And?

08:50.964 --> 08:53.598
That's it. What she said is...

08:53.600 --> 08:54.799
It's true.

08:55.102 --> 08:56.201
What's true?

08:58.138 --> 09:00.805
I've only been
with one person...

09:02.075 --> 09:03.275
...in my entire life.

09:05.312 --> 09:06.778
And that was Ronnie,

09:06.780 --> 09:08.613
on the night that
he died five years ago.

09:09.983 --> 09:14.819
So, when I got pregnant,
I was scared and confused,

09:14.821 --> 09:18.123
and I didn't understand
how it was possible.

09:20.961 --> 09:22.027
But now I do.

09:22.896 --> 09:26.231
Some strange
miracle has happened

09:27.200 --> 09:28.833
because of Ronnie.

09:29.870 --> 09:31.036
'Cause of our love.

09:32.072 --> 09:33.171
This baby...

09:34.975 --> 09:36.708
This baby inside of me belongs

09:37.144 --> 09:38.310
to Ronnie.

09:40.047 --> 09:41.613
It's his.

09:48.655 --> 09:50.155
Get her out of my house.

10:07.074 --> 10:08.974
Why are you doing this?

10:08.976 --> 10:10.675
You guys just deserve to know.

10:11.111 --> 10:12.277
Melissa,

10:13.347 --> 10:15.013
it's not possible.

10:15.015 --> 10:17.115
I'm not crazy, okay?

10:17.985 --> 10:19.250
I'm not stupid...

10:22.956 --> 10:24.990
It's just the only
answer that there is.

10:25.359 --> 10:26.725
Is it?

10:26.727 --> 10:29.227
Since the accident, I get these

10:29.229 --> 10:31.663
spells, these blackouts...
Just stop.

10:31.665 --> 10:35.800
And I can feel Ronnie.
Stop.

10:35.802 --> 10:37.936
It's how I knew
to see the psychic.
Stop!

10:46.413 --> 10:49.781
You ever wanna talk, or...

10:52.786 --> 10:54.786
Come see the baby,

10:54.788 --> 10:57.789
I'm living in a small cottage
off Muxhull Road.

10:58.425 --> 10:59.891
It's my cellphone number.

11:12.739 --> 11:14.005
He likes your photos.

11:16.810 --> 11:18.209
That's something.

11:22.716 --> 11:23.848
(DOOR CLOSES)

11:34.461 --> 11:35.860
(SIGHS)

11:45.038 --> 11:47.338
RONNIE:<i> How's my tie?</i>
<i> It feels awful.</i>

11:47.340 --> 11:48.707
PHILIP:<i> It's a tie.</i>

11:48.709 --> 11:50.742
It's tied. Big night.

11:52.345 --> 11:53.912
Don't be nervous.

11:53.914 --> 11:56.347
You wanna give me some tips?
I don't know...

11:56.349 --> 11:57.816
Don't mess it up.

12:01.121 --> 12:03.288
Wow.
Wow.

12:03.290 --> 12:05.156
Where's the glass slipper?

12:05.158 --> 12:06.958
Shut up.
You look amazing.

12:06.960 --> 12:08.610
Okay, let's get a picture.

12:08.611 --> 12:10.261
No, we're gonna be late.
Can I just take some
when we get there?

12:10.263 --> 12:12.497
RICHARD: Oh, no, no.
One for your mom. Come on.

12:12.499 --> 12:16.267
Next year at this time, you're
gonna be in the city with all
your friends,

12:16.269 --> 12:18.103
we need something
to remember you by.

12:18.105 --> 12:19.804
One picture.
All right, one picture.

12:19.806 --> 12:21.072
Okay.

12:21.074 --> 12:22.507
Let Phil take it though,
so it's doesn't suck.

12:22.509 --> 12:24.109
Hey!

12:24.111 --> 12:27.178
The man has a point.
RICHARD: Big smiles.
Big smiles.

12:27.981 --> 12:29.314
There it is.
Okay.

12:29.316 --> 12:30.882
Call me if you need anything.

12:30.884 --> 12:32.350
I will.

12:32.352 --> 12:35.153
You have fun tonight, all right.
That's your job.

12:36.223 --> 12:38.256
You look great.

12:38.258 --> 12:41.092
Hey, lovebirds!
Shall we get this on the road?

12:41.094 --> 12:42.427
You're gonna be at
Kiera and Gordon's, right?

12:42.429 --> 12:44.863
Yeah. You're gonna be there?
I'll see you there.

12:46.166 --> 12:48.233
See you guys.

12:48.235 --> 12:50.902
RICHARD: Have fun.
CHARLENE: My baby.

12:53.373 --> 12:54.939
CHARLENE: Take care!

12:54.941 --> 12:56.474
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

12:56.476 --> 12:57.809
Bye.

13:01.348 --> 13:02.547
(SIGHS)

13:02.549 --> 13:03.948
You all right?

13:03.950 --> 13:05.884
(CHUCKLING)

13:05.886 --> 13:07.118
I'm still here, you know?

13:07.120 --> 13:09.187
Yeah, yeah, well obviously...

13:09.189 --> 13:11.923
All right, ready?
One, two, and...

13:11.925 --> 13:13.191
(CAMERA CLICKS)

13:57.237 --> 13:58.570
Hi, honey.

13:59.339 --> 14:01.156
Hi, Gail.

14:01.157 --> 14:02.974
You look like you could
use some ice tea.

14:03.610 --> 14:04.909
Perfect.

14:06.346 --> 14:08.079
Thank you for letting
me borrow the car.

14:08.081 --> 14:11.583
Oh, you kidding? Whatever Bill
and I can do to help you.

14:11.585 --> 14:13.885
You don't have to go
through this alone.

14:15.889 --> 14:17.555
I won't be alone soon enough.

14:18.425 --> 14:19.958
Can I?

14:20.560 --> 14:21.993
Of course.

14:25.232 --> 14:27.465
(GASPS) Oh, that was a big one.

14:28.068 --> 14:30.068
Oh!

14:30.070 --> 14:33.037
It doesn't hurt, huh?
Sometimes, but...

14:34.074 --> 14:35.273
I kind of like it.

14:35.275 --> 14:37.141
Makes me feel
like we're talking.

14:39.312 --> 14:40.411
(SIGHS IN RELIEF)

14:40.413 --> 14:43.147
Now, I do worry
about your driving,

14:43.149 --> 14:45.550
having one of your blackouts.

14:45.551 --> 14:47.952
It's been five months
and the doctor says it
probably won't happen again.

14:49.522 --> 14:51.256
Well!
Ah!

14:51.258 --> 14:53.925
If it isn't my two favorite
people in the world.

14:53.927 --> 14:55.660
Oh. Sorry. Two and a half.

14:55.662 --> 14:56.928
(GAIL LAUGHS)

14:56.930 --> 14:58.630
Oh, Bill, you've been smoking?

14:58.632 --> 15:00.231
No, if you're
smelling something,

15:00.233 --> 15:01.966
it's because I was helping

15:01.968 --> 15:04.535
Rafael load up the truck.
Yeah, right.

15:04.537 --> 15:07.138
That man is a chimney with legs.
Hmm.

15:07.140 --> 15:09.040
Come on. You can
frisk me if you want.

15:09.042 --> 15:11.976
I'm cooking.
Go on, check out my pockets.

15:11.978 --> 15:14.145
Give me a quick once over.
Melissa won't mind, right?

15:14.147 --> 15:15.380
Might be kind of fun to watch.

15:15.382 --> 15:16.581
Enough out of you two.

15:16.583 --> 15:18.650
Okay, I believe you.
You're not smoking.

15:18.652 --> 15:20.084
Go, sit down.

15:22.122 --> 15:24.923
So, what's for dinner?

15:24.925 --> 15:28.526
These new kids, they can't tell
a half inch from a quarter.

15:28.528 --> 15:32.196
Every damn time they pull out
a ruler, the line gets longer

15:32.198 --> 15:34.332
and the customers get angrier.

15:34.334 --> 15:36.534
You're the last
good worker I've got.

15:36.536 --> 15:38.536
Hmm.
We're gonna miss you.

15:38.538 --> 15:41.172
I'll just be gone
a couple of months, I mean,

15:41.174 --> 15:44.342
once the baby comes,
I'll be back in no time.

15:46.313 --> 15:47.679
That's actually something that

15:47.681 --> 15:49.514
I wanted to talk
to you guys about.

15:50.717 --> 15:52.583
Since my parents aren't, uh...

15:52.585 --> 15:55.253
Since they've chosen
not to be involved,

15:56.690 --> 16:00.558
I was wondering...
I was hoping that

16:00.560 --> 16:03.695
maybe you two would
be the guardians<i> ad litem.</i>

16:05.165 --> 16:07.165
It's just in case
something goes wrong,

16:07.167 --> 16:09.334
and I can't make a decision,

16:09.335 --> 16:11.502
then you guys would be
in charge of me, and...

16:12.372 --> 16:15.540
And the baby.
Are you sure?

16:15.542 --> 16:21.079
Yeah.
I mean, you don't wanna
try to contact the father?

16:21.081 --> 16:25.216
BILL: Gail?
I mean, a child needs a family.

16:25.218 --> 16:28.019
You guys are the closest thing
that I have to a family.

16:33.593 --> 16:34.993
We'd be honored.

16:34.995 --> 16:36.094
(GAIL CHUCKLES)

16:36.429 --> 16:37.495
Yes.

16:40.166 --> 16:41.265
It's just in case.

16:42.535 --> 16:44.035
(TV PLAYING)

16:48.241 --> 16:50.008
MAN 1: (ON TV)<i> I do.</i>
<i> Her name's Akesha.</i>

16:50.010 --> 16:51.476
MAN 2: (ON TV)
<i> Akesha? Beautiful.</i>

16:51.478 --> 16:54.629
<i> You didn't chose it?</i>

16:54.630 --> 16:57.781
<i> MAN 1: No. She's almost</i>
<i> two years old,</i>
<i> and I have to tell you this,</i>

16:57.784 --> 17:00.351
<i> she did this most amazing</i>
<i> thing yesterday.</i>

17:00.353 --> 17:03.221
<i> MAN 2: Does this</i>
<i> involve diapers</i>
<i> because we recently had...</i>

17:03.223 --> 17:05.807
<i> MAN 1: No, no.</i>
<i> It's very clean.</i>
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

17:05.808 --> 17:08.392
<i> She has this doll,</i>
<i> and she sucks on his fingers,</i>
<i> of course.</i>

17:08.395 --> 17:12.463
<i> MAN 2: Okay, stop. You clearly</i>
<i> promised that it was</i>
<i> going to be a clean story.</i>

17:12.465 --> 17:17.035
<i> You're not allowed to...</i>
MAN 1:<i> So I'm putting</i>
<i> her down for a nap,</i>

17:17.037 --> 17:19.303
<i> she's sucking on his fingers,</i>

17:19.305 --> 17:22.807
<i> and she starts to sing</i>
Itsy Bitsy Spider,
<i> so I'm singing it too...</i>

17:22.809 --> 17:25.309
(STATIC)

17:25.311 --> 17:27.612
Why would you say that?
(GLASS CRACKS)

17:44.631 --> 17:45.830
What happened to your hand?

17:45.832 --> 17:47.465
Cut it.

17:47.467 --> 17:49.600
So you duct taped it?
It's what I had.

17:49.602 --> 17:51.302
You wanna talk about my hand?

17:51.304 --> 17:53.237
After that, we'll talk
about your leg, okay?

18:04.517 --> 18:05.616
Hmm.

18:05.618 --> 18:09.520
Isn't this a healthy
start to the morning?

18:09.522 --> 18:12.423
Why do you have to be so
sarcastic?
Oh, you think I'm...

18:14.494 --> 18:16.427
You know what, forget it.

18:16.429 --> 18:18.863
You're obviously still
upset about yesterday.

18:18.865 --> 18:21.332
You're a selfish young man.

18:21.334 --> 18:23.601
That's what I've raised,
a selfish young man.

18:23.603 --> 18:25.336
This woman...

18:25.338 --> 18:28.539
this girl get herself knocked up
and then comes stalking around,

18:28.541 --> 18:30.875
pointing the finger
at my dead son.

18:30.877 --> 18:32.610
As far as I'm concerned,
I let her off easy.

18:32.612 --> 18:34.812
I should have called the cops.
Fascinating.

18:37.517 --> 18:38.749
You're on her side?

18:40.820 --> 18:41.886
Philip?

18:43.590 --> 18:45.323
Why are you on her side?

18:45.892 --> 18:47.391
Philip, hey!

18:47.393 --> 18:49.494
Why are you on her side?

18:49.496 --> 18:52.113
I'm not on anybody's side.

18:52.114 --> 18:54.731
There's no side to have.
Both, you and Melissa
are equally delusional.

18:54.734 --> 18:57.435
That is my point.
It is completely impossible.

18:57.437 --> 19:00.204
Well, it's not
completely impossible.

19:00.206 --> 19:02.056
You are on her side.

19:02.057 --> 19:03.907
Okay, I'm not saying that I
believe her. All I'm saying

19:03.910 --> 19:05.593
is that if you think about it,

19:05.594 --> 19:07.277
there's a chance that
what she said is true.

19:07.881 --> 19:10.581
Then explain it to me. Please.

19:12.252 --> 19:13.484
Look, if...

19:14.254 --> 19:16.438
it's a big if,

19:16.439 --> 19:18.623
Ronnie's sperm was somehow
frozen before he died,

19:18.625 --> 19:21.893
there's a chance that Melissa
could've used it, and
impregnated herself,

19:21.895 --> 19:24.762
years later, and thus
we would have Ronnie's baby.

19:25.698 --> 19:27.431
That's ridiculous.

19:27.433 --> 19:29.934
He was a teenager with
his whole life ahead of him,

19:29.936 --> 19:31.402
why would he do that?

19:32.305 --> 19:33.871
Philip?

19:33.873 --> 19:35.439
PHILIP: Someone's in here.

19:39.512 --> 19:40.845
People do it all the time.

19:40.847 --> 19:43.381
What people?
I don't know, ma, people.

19:43.383 --> 19:44.515
Friends of yours?

19:44.517 --> 19:45.616
(SCOFFS)

19:45.618 --> 19:47.785
Philip?

19:47.787 --> 19:49.620
You need to get a grip,
and give it up.

19:49.622 --> 19:54.458
Oh, okay, yeah,
just, just walk away.

19:54.460 --> 19:57.895
CHARLENE: You're just gonna
block it out of your mind?
Just like that?

19:57.897 --> 19:59.664
Well, I can't do that.

20:02.735 --> 20:06.404
This is my son she's talking
about, Philip. Your brother.

20:24.224 --> 20:26.457
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

20:56.322 --> 20:57.722
Where's the computer lab?

20:57.724 --> 21:00.625
Used to be right there.
Now it's some sorta Starbucks?

21:00.627 --> 21:01.826
Charlene?

21:02.662 --> 21:04.495
Pillia.

21:04.497 --> 21:06.030
It's okay, Bailey, I've got it.

21:08.268 --> 21:09.734
It's been a while.

21:09.736 --> 21:11.502
How are you?

21:11.504 --> 21:13.004
Everyday's a blessing.

21:14.474 --> 21:15.906
Where's the computer lab?

21:15.908 --> 21:17.908
We scaled back
the lab years ago.

21:18.811 --> 21:20.711
Why don't you just follow me.

21:20.713 --> 21:22.780
We got a grant
to digitize all the pre-articles

21:22.782 --> 21:24.582
and research papers
going back six years.

21:24.584 --> 21:26.717
So, whatever you're
looking to research,

21:26.719 --> 21:29.837
it'll be relatively
easy to find.

21:29.838 --> 21:32.956
I'm the highest credentialed
librarian this institution has,
or will ever see.

21:32.959 --> 21:34.892
I know how to use a search bar.

21:34.894 --> 21:35.993
(CARD ALARM)

21:38.998 --> 21:40.865
(CARD ALARM)

21:40.867 --> 21:44.635
The system resets itself
every few years if
the cards aren't used.

21:45.438 --> 21:47.004
So, I'll update it.

21:48.408 --> 21:49.774
You can use mine for now.

21:51.577 --> 21:52.843
(CARD BEEPS)

21:52.845 --> 21:55.012
Now, there are some tricks
to these searches.

21:55.014 --> 21:57.081
For example, what are you
looking to research?

21:57.083 --> 21:59.650
I don't see how
that's any of your business.

21:59.652 --> 22:02.920
Right. Okay, well, if you need
me, you know where to find me.

22:02.922 --> 22:04.422
Sitting behind my desk.

22:06.392 --> 22:08.492
It's good to see
you again, Charlene.

22:24.944 --> 22:27.345
MAN:<i> After the ejaculate</i>
<i> has been donated,</i>

22:27.347 --> 22:28.946
<i> and the sperm bottled,</i>
<i> and collected.</i>

22:28.948 --> 22:31.515
<i> Cryo protectives are added,</i>
<i> and the sperm is frozen...</i>

22:42.395 --> 22:44.495
"Medically assisted
reproduction...

22:48.801 --> 22:51.102
"Recent advances
allow for collection

22:51.104 --> 22:54.805
"of sperm samples to occur
for up to 24 hours after death."

22:59.011 --> 23:00.644
After death.

23:10.923 --> 23:12.523
(CAMERA CLICKING)

24:02.909 --> 24:04.575
(TIRES SCREECHING)

24:09.182 --> 24:10.481
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

24:12.885 --> 24:14.618
(TIRES SQUEALING)

24:25.097 --> 24:27.164
CHAZ: Four wheel driver,
all-standard features...

24:27.967 --> 24:30.668
Excuse me, I'll be right back.

24:30.670 --> 24:34.672
(CLEARS THROAT) Let me guess,
you're looking for something
safe. Am I right?

24:35.608 --> 24:37.708
Oh, shit!

24:37.710 --> 24:41.979
Phillie C. How you doing, man?
Chaz.

24:41.981 --> 24:43.747
It's good to see you.

24:43.749 --> 24:46.250
(CLEARS THROAT)
Yeah. Sweats and tee,
casual choice.

24:46.252 --> 24:48.619
I like it. I like it.

24:48.621 --> 24:50.921
What's up with the leg, man?

24:50.923 --> 24:54.625
Uh, bike accident.
I was going up Broadway,

24:54.627 --> 24:58.262
and some asshole in a
convertible ran a red doing 50.

24:58.264 --> 25:00.664
(SIGHS)
Yeah.

25:00.666 --> 25:03.033
Lucky it was just your leg.
Yeah.

25:03.569 --> 25:05.169
Yeah, I know.

25:05.171 --> 25:07.238
So, what are you looking at?

25:07.240 --> 25:10.107
What?
What kind of car?

25:10.109 --> 25:12.576
I can hook you up. Junior
Salesman as of last month.

25:12.578 --> 25:14.812
Wow.
40k base,

25:14.814 --> 25:19.049
commissions on top, and I can
take any one of these bad boys
out for the night.

25:19.051 --> 25:20.951
Impress the ladies.

25:20.952 --> 25:22.852
So, you and Stacy
aren't still together?

25:22.855 --> 25:27.291
We still see each other, but
it's not, you know, exclusive.

25:27.293 --> 25:30.261
Right.
Come on, I'll show
you the good stuff.

25:30.997 --> 25:32.563
Hey, what about Melissa?

25:33.032 --> 25:34.965
You still talk to her?

25:35.768 --> 25:37.101
It's been a bit.

25:37.103 --> 25:38.886
She kind of freaked out

25:38.887 --> 25:40.670
after what happened.
You know, blamed herself.

25:41.908 --> 25:43.974
So, what is she doing now?

25:44.744 --> 25:46.243
She dating anybody?

25:46.245 --> 25:48.429
Don't think so.

25:48.430 --> 25:50.614
To be honest, I don't really
think she moved on at all.

25:50.616 --> 25:52.850
Her parents kicked
her out a few years back.

25:52.852 --> 25:54.585
So she's not really
in the loop anymore.

25:54.587 --> 25:56.053
Why'd her parents kick her out?

25:56.055 --> 25:58.556
Some tight-ass
Christian bullshit.

25:58.558 --> 26:01.959
Her pop got pissed off at all
that magic stuff she was into.

26:01.961 --> 26:03.794
Magic?

26:03.796 --> 26:04.995
What do you mean?

26:06.032 --> 26:09.099
I don't know,
she as always going on about

26:09.101 --> 26:12.836
talking to the dead,
contacting spirits,
re-incarnation.

26:12.838 --> 26:16.040
She wanted to talk
to Ronnie again, you know?

26:16.042 --> 26:19.009
Oh, but Stacy saw her down at
the hardware store last month,

26:19.345 --> 26:21.178
prego.
Prego?

26:21.180 --> 26:23.347
Wow.
So...

26:23.349 --> 26:24.815
She must be dating somebody,

26:24.817 --> 26:27.351
right? At least
for a couple minutes.

26:27.353 --> 26:29.853
You want her number?
I bet Stace still has it.

26:29.855 --> 26:31.889
No. I was just wondering.

26:31.891 --> 26:33.290
You sure?
Yeah.

26:33.292 --> 26:35.326
You two always had a thing.

26:36.929 --> 26:38.362
Hey, no, no, it's cool.

26:38.364 --> 26:39.697
I just mean, Ronnie
would have liked

26:39.699 --> 26:41.632
you looking out
for her, that's all.

26:52.745 --> 26:54.028
(PHONE LINE RINGING)

26:54.029 --> 26:55.312
WOMAN:<i> South Miami Hospital,</i>
<i> fertility Clinic.</i>

26:55.314 --> 26:56.814
Dr. Richard Chase.

26:56.816 --> 26:58.782
WOMAN:<i> Who's calling please?</i>
His wife.

26:58.784 --> 27:01.318
WOMAN:<i> Is this urgent?</i>
Yes, it's urgent.

27:01.320 --> 27:04.955
Cathy at the front desk,
she'll put something
in the books for next month.

27:04.957 --> 27:07.725
But, looks really good.

27:10.129 --> 27:13.364
Dr. Chase, your wife's on the
phone. She says it's urgent.

27:14.066 --> 27:16.500
Holly, what's wrong?

27:16.501 --> 27:18.935
CHARLENE:<i> Wrong wife.</i>
<i> But you sure</i>
<i> answered quickly, didn't you?</i>

27:18.938 --> 27:21.939
For Christs' sake, Charlene,
you can't do that.

27:21.941 --> 27:23.340
I was with a patient.

27:23.342 --> 27:25.643
Can you freeze sperm?
You're calling me for what?

27:25.645 --> 27:28.779
Can you freeze sperm?
<i> Of course, you can freeze it.</i>

27:28.781 --> 27:30.681
Post mortem?

27:30.683 --> 27:32.282
<i> Yeah, it's been done. Yes.</i>

27:32.284 --> 27:35.019
By anyone you know?
What are you driving at?

27:35.021 --> 27:37.087
<i> We had a visit</i>
<i> from Melissa Moody.</i>

27:37.089 --> 27:38.155
<i> She's pregnant.</i>

27:38.157 --> 27:40.357
But, wait, it gets better.

27:42.294 --> 27:44.428
I'll call you back.

27:44.430 --> 27:47.264
None of what you're saying makes
any sense. It's impossible.

27:47.266 --> 27:49.099
CHARLENE:<i> Yeah, welcome</i>
<i> to the goddamn club.</i>

27:49.101 --> 27:51.669
But then Philip got me thinking,
and so I did some research,

27:51.671 --> 27:54.038
"Post Mortem Cryogenic
Preservation."

27:54.040 --> 27:56.206
You think Melissa
froze Ronnie's sperm?

27:56.208 --> 27:58.442
<i> Well, who was working the night</i>
<i> they brought Ronnie in?</i>

27:58.444 --> 28:00.745
Oh, yes, that was you.

28:00.746 --> 28:03.047
And then I thought, that just
the sort of freak stunt my
husband would pull.

28:03.049 --> 28:05.366
That would be ex-husband.

28:05.367 --> 28:07.684
<i> Ex-husband. Trust me,</i>
<i> I thank God for that everyday,</i>

28:07.687 --> 28:10.187
and now you're acting cagey,
so I know something's up.

28:10.189 --> 28:12.423
<i> Okay, so let me make sure</i>
<i> I got this straight,</i>

28:12.425 --> 28:15.325
you believe that I
extracted Ronnie's sperm,

28:15.327 --> 28:19.363
after her was dead,
and I froze it, and I put it in
Melissa nine months ago?

28:19.365 --> 28:21.398
<i> The girl knew you</i>
<i> lived in Florida.</i>

28:21.400 --> 28:23.767
Why is that?
<i> I have no idea.</i>

28:23.769 --> 28:27.104
So you haven't seen her,
or spoken to her?

28:27.106 --> 28:29.006
What's this really about?
You want me to come up there?

28:29.008 --> 28:30.240
Oh, you'd like that,
wouldn't you?

28:30.242 --> 28:31.975
White Knight
riding up in his horse.

28:31.977 --> 28:34.278
No. You stay down there
with Malibu Barbie.

28:34.280 --> 28:36.046
Don't bring Holly into this.

28:37.149 --> 28:38.215
Hello?

28:50.796 --> 28:52.129
(DOOR OPENING)

28:55.101 --> 28:57.101
Look who's home early.

29:00.372 --> 29:01.371
Hey.

29:01.372 --> 29:02.371
Couldn't live
without me, could ya?

29:07.313 --> 29:09.046
Bad day?
No.

29:10.149 --> 29:12.216
Feinstein baby, delivered early.

29:12.218 --> 29:13.383
It's a boy.

29:14.186 --> 29:15.385
<i> Mazel tov.</i>

29:19.058 --> 29:20.424
Charlene called.

29:21.193 --> 29:23.026
Little off the deep end.

29:23.028 --> 29:25.262
And she's usually
pretty hostile, but

29:25.264 --> 29:28.132
she seemed...
I don't know, scared.

29:29.101 --> 29:30.818
Of what?

29:30.819 --> 29:32.536
Communication
is not her strong suit.

29:32.538 --> 29:33.971
So, I don't know.

29:35.107 --> 29:37.808
I'm sure it's nothing.
I'm sure you're right.

29:39.879 --> 29:42.012
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

29:45.151 --> 29:47.985
Knock-knock. Room service.
Oh!

29:54.260 --> 29:56.060
What did you do to this?

29:56.061 --> 29:57.861
It's sugar free. I was hoping
you wouldn't notice.

29:57.863 --> 30:00.798
Well, you might as well slap me
on the face and call it a kiss.

30:00.800 --> 30:02.399
(COUGHING)

30:02.401 --> 30:06.236
Darling, you've got to see
a doctor about this cough.

30:06.238 --> 30:08.572
Don't look at me
like that, I'm fine.

30:08.574 --> 30:12.109
All right, well, please
don't stay out too late.

30:12.111 --> 30:14.845
The floor won't fix itself.
Yeah.

30:14.847 --> 30:18.081
Are you gonna drink that?
Yeah, I'm drinking. Thank you.

30:18.884 --> 30:20.517
Hurry up.

30:20.519 --> 30:22.853
Five more boards,
then I'm done.

30:36.936 --> 30:38.335
(PHONE VIBRATING)

30:51.217 --> 30:53.984
Hey, dad.
Hey, buddy, how you doing?

30:53.986 --> 30:55.319
<i> Same old, same old.</i>

30:55.321 --> 30:57.354
Yeah? How's the leg holding up?

30:58.424 --> 30:59.523
It's still attached.

30:59.525 --> 31:03.627
Well, good. Hopefully you're
getting outta the house,

31:03.629 --> 31:06.063
finding a few good shots?

31:06.065 --> 31:07.931
<i> Camera's still busted up, so...</i>

31:07.933 --> 31:10.534
I'm pretty much stuck inside
staring at contact sheets.

31:10.536 --> 31:12.469
<i> Oh, listen, if you</i>
<i> need a new camera,</i>

31:12.471 --> 31:14.471
I'm happy to do it, okay?

31:14.473 --> 31:15.639
It's no big deal.

31:15.641 --> 31:17.574
It's okay. I got it covered.

31:19.612 --> 31:21.912
I spoke to your mom.

31:21.914 --> 31:24.448
She, um,
she told me about Melissa.

31:24.450 --> 31:26.283
<i> I bet she did.</i>

31:26.285 --> 31:27.918
Kind of threw mom for a loop.

31:29.021 --> 31:31.555
How did she
seem to you? Melissa?

31:31.557 --> 31:33.257
<i> Seems pretty damn pregnant.</i>

31:33.259 --> 31:35.659
No, no, no. I mean, you know...

31:36.662 --> 31:38.262
does she seem stable?

31:38.264 --> 31:41.531
Just bringing up
Ronnie like that, and

31:41.533 --> 31:43.500
not saying who the father was.

31:43.502 --> 31:47.404
<i> I don't know,</i>
<i> things seemed pretty strange.</i>

31:47.406 --> 31:49.206
But I don't think
it's our problem.

31:50.109 --> 31:53.343
No. No, of course, not.

31:55.481 --> 31:57.281
It's not. I just, um...

31:58.317 --> 31:59.383
Look, I just wanted
to check on you,

31:59.385 --> 32:01.051
and see how guys
are holding up.

32:01.053 --> 32:03.387
<i> Yeah, well,</i>
<i> mom's gone off the reservation.</i>

32:04.023 --> 32:05.589
I can barely take a piss

32:05.590 --> 32:07.156
without getting it
all over myself, so...

32:07.693 --> 32:08.959
Yeah,

32:09.628 --> 32:11.161
things are not the best.

32:11.964 --> 32:14.048
Listen,

32:14.049 --> 32:16.133
Philip, if you need anything,
I just want you to ask.

32:16.135 --> 32:18.035
Okay, I'm here for you.

32:18.037 --> 32:20.137
Sure, dad. Got it.

32:22.241 --> 32:23.974
Tell Holly I say hi.

32:23.976 --> 32:27.544
I will. Take care of yourself.
I love you.

32:27.546 --> 32:28.979
<i> Yeah, you too.</i>

32:36.422 --> 32:38.355
(PHONE RINGING)

32:38.356 --> 32:40.289
<i> Hello, Bill's Hardware.</i>
Bill Harmen, please.

33:08.220 --> 33:09.453
(DOOR CLOSING)

33:09.455 --> 33:10.654
Mom?

33:11.523 --> 33:13.323
Is that you?

33:13.325 --> 33:16.093
CHARLENE: I brought dinner.
Come down.

33:19.298 --> 33:20.697
Coming.

33:38.217 --> 33:39.516
(MUSIC PLAYING)

34:14.420 --> 34:17.587
No one likes a nosey neighbor.

34:17.589 --> 34:20.090
I was just cleaning up.
Uh-huh.

34:21.560 --> 34:24.261
She seems happy, right?
Why not?

34:25.230 --> 34:26.296
Baby on the way.

34:26.298 --> 34:28.532
Yeah, but she's all alone.

34:28.534 --> 34:31.301
Why won't she tell us
who the father is.

34:31.303 --> 34:34.104
She has her own life to lead.

34:34.106 --> 34:37.441
It doesn't matter
you don't approve.
That's not what I meant.

34:37.443 --> 34:39.627
She's not our daughter.

34:39.628 --> 34:41.812
We open ourselves up,
do what we can. Let her get on.

34:42.614 --> 34:44.114
You'll see.

34:44.750 --> 34:46.516
Everything will be okay.

34:47.853 --> 34:49.286
Hmm.

35:02.468 --> 35:04.234
I'm off to the library.

35:04.236 --> 35:05.702
Really?
Really.

35:05.704 --> 35:08.171
What are your big plans?
Solve world hunger.

35:08.440 --> 35:09.639
Smart ass.

35:11.643 --> 35:12.709
(DOOR CLOSES)

35:17.249 --> 35:18.381
(CAR DOOR SHUTS)

35:20.752 --> 35:22.152
(ENGINE REVVING)

36:37.796 --> 36:39.729
Gum is for the children.

36:39.731 --> 36:41.331
You're welcome
to have a piece if you like.

36:41.333 --> 36:44.634
Sorry, I'm looking for a woman

36:45.737 --> 36:47.971
named Chantel.
Chantrel.

36:48.607 --> 36:50.240
You found her.

36:50.242 --> 36:51.308
Philip.

36:51.310 --> 36:53.510
Now you're doing my job for me.

36:54.680 --> 36:57.681
You had a client recently

36:58.550 --> 37:00.717
named Melissa. She was pregnant.

37:00.719 --> 37:04.654
I can't talk about others
who've come for my guidance, but

37:04.656 --> 37:06.856
you're welcome to come
and have a session for yourself.

37:06.858 --> 37:08.992
No, thank you.

37:10.362 --> 37:11.928
What happened to your leg?

37:13.265 --> 37:14.965
I don't wanna do
your job for you.

37:14.967 --> 37:17.434
I'm a psychic, not a surgeon.

37:19.738 --> 37:21.871
But I can tell it
embarrasses you.

37:23.675 --> 37:25.442
And you lie about it.

37:29.748 --> 37:32.616
PILLIA: You're like
a regular visitor now.

37:32.618 --> 37:35.919
Yeah, well,
I'm doing research on children.

37:35.921 --> 37:37.887
I might be a grandmother soon.

37:37.889 --> 37:38.989
Might?

37:39.691 --> 37:41.291
Congratulations.

37:44.263 --> 37:45.662
Well, I should get going.

37:47.366 --> 37:49.466
I didn't steal
your job, Charlene.

37:51.837 --> 37:54.537
You didn't show up
for six months.

37:54.539 --> 37:57.307
The place was going downhill.
Someone had to take over.

38:00.279 --> 38:01.544
I know.

38:03.782 --> 38:06.416
So... what now?

38:06.418 --> 38:07.917
You, um,

38:07.919 --> 38:09.586
you tell my future?

38:09.588 --> 38:11.755
The future hasn't happened yet.

38:11.757 --> 38:14.391
I tell your present.
The parts you can't see.

38:18.063 --> 38:19.829
I'd like a strand of your hair.

38:19.831 --> 38:22.699
A strand of my...
Watch.

38:27.973 --> 38:29.506
Okay!

38:30.375 --> 38:32.425
What is that for?

38:32.426 --> 38:34.476
The things we see,
and feel, and do,

38:34.479 --> 38:36.346
they stay inside us.

38:36.348 --> 38:40.583
Joy and pain lives on
long after you experience it.

38:40.585 --> 38:43.953
It's the same
for everyone, everything.

38:43.955 --> 38:45.989
We carry it alike.

38:45.991 --> 38:49.359
Man, bird, fly...

38:49.361 --> 38:51.361
what lives in one,

38:51.363 --> 38:54.564
can live in another.
That's what connects us.

38:56.501 --> 38:58.001
That's what gives us strength.

39:04.543 --> 39:06.376
You think about Ronnie often.

39:11.016 --> 39:13.917
He's here?
No.

39:13.919 --> 39:18.021
But Melissa had
a boyfriend Ronnie, right?

39:18.023 --> 39:19.956
And Ronnie
had a brother, Philip?

39:22.127 --> 39:24.761
Half this job
is just having a good memory.

39:32.137 --> 39:33.837
Your pain is deep.

39:34.973 --> 39:36.740
But it's different than hers.

39:38.610 --> 39:42.145
This emptiness,
it's not gonna go away,

39:42.147 --> 39:44.714
because you're not
ready to be whole.

39:44.716 --> 39:48.551
You've tied yourself
to the world around you, but

39:48.553 --> 39:52.555
there's more answers than
those you can touch and see.

39:55.460 --> 39:59.996
You don't believe we live
in a world beyond this one.

40:00.665 --> 40:02.899
What, like ghosts?

40:02.901 --> 40:05.168
It's alright, you don't have
to believe in ghosts.

40:06.071 --> 40:08.872
I do. That's my truth.

40:10.008 --> 40:15.078
And Melissa believes,
and it's true for her.

40:15.080 --> 40:18.081
But the question is,
what do you believe in?

40:22.454 --> 40:25.688
That's why you're running from
the things you find difficult.

40:26.825 --> 40:29.526
The things you find painful,

40:29.528 --> 40:32.128
you ignore, or ridicule.

40:33.498 --> 40:36.599
That's why you've
given up on yourself.
Okay...

40:36.601 --> 40:39.869
And you've
given up on everyone else.

40:41.440 --> 40:44.073
Find your truth,
whatever or whoever that is.

40:44.075 --> 40:46.943
Only then will you walk out
of the shadows.

40:57.489 --> 41:00.523
I'm not supposed
to be telling you this.

41:01.860 --> 41:03.226
He says that,

41:03.228 --> 41:05.161
there's a chance
you could get hurt.

41:05.163 --> 41:06.629
Who says?

41:07.165 --> 41:08.231
Ronnie?

41:08.233 --> 41:11.601
There could be
trouble for you...

41:13.138 --> 41:15.038
For those you're close to.

41:32.891 --> 41:34.123
That's it.

41:36.895 --> 41:38.695
You know what you have to do.

41:42.767 --> 41:44.901
I take Visa and Mastercard.

42:03.522 --> 42:05.522
Oh, can I help you?

42:05.524 --> 42:07.624
Hi, I'm looking
for Melissa Moody?

42:07.626 --> 42:11.861
Her cottage is in the back,
but she's at work right now.

42:11.863 --> 42:13.963
Oh, okay.
You would be?

42:14.799 --> 42:16.666
I'm Charlene Chase.

42:16.668 --> 42:19.135
Ronnie is-- was my son.

42:19.137 --> 42:21.604
Melissa's boyfriend.
I'm so glad to meet you.

42:21.606 --> 42:24.574
God, Melissa's...

42:24.576 --> 42:30.547
really a wonderful girl, and she
speaks very lovingly of Ronnie.

42:30.549 --> 42:33.583
Thank you.
Everything that you
have done for her...

42:34.886 --> 42:36.819
Above and beyond
the call of duty...

42:37.989 --> 42:40.056
I'm sorry?
The rent for the cottage.

42:40.058 --> 42:43.192
Dr. Chase sends that
cheque every month.

42:43.194 --> 42:44.794
Right on time.

42:48.133 --> 42:49.866
I'm sorry...

42:51.303 --> 42:55.805
I get confused.
Mrs. Chase? I'm sorry...

42:56.808 --> 42:58.525
Calm down, or I'm hanging up.

42:58.526 --> 43:00.243
No, no, no. You don't get
to tell me what to do.

43:00.245 --> 43:02.312
Look, I have done nothing
to you, not a thing,

43:02.314 --> 43:04.814
if you want Richard
to call you back...
<i> Listen, you little tramp,</i>

43:04.816 --> 43:07.350
you put that lying sack of shit
on the phone right now.

43:07.352 --> 43:09.352
Or so help me god,
I will come down to Florida

43:09.354 --> 43:10.887
and shove a palm tree up that

43:10.889 --> 43:12.756
perfectly bleached
asshole of yours!

43:12.757 --> 43:14.624
<i> He's gone to New York!</i>
<i> He's gone to see you!</i>

43:25.203 --> 43:26.369
(HUMMING)

43:42.020 --> 43:43.152
Ah!

43:54.399 --> 43:56.366
Oh, you've got to be kidding me.

44:17.022 --> 44:18.354
Thank you for stopping by.

44:24.129 --> 44:26.295
Who's that?
It's Gail.

44:26.297 --> 44:28.097
If it isn't my favorite person.

44:28.099 --> 44:32.368
Yeah, so, I was just down in the
basement doing some laundry...

44:32.370 --> 44:35.872
Rafael! You need
to restock the mops, okay?

44:36.675 --> 44:38.007
Sorry, hon, go on.

44:38.009 --> 44:39.909
<i> Yeah, and then</i>
<i> I was coming back out</i>

44:39.911 --> 44:42.178
and a sock rolled on the floor.

44:44.149 --> 44:45.214
And...

44:46.751 --> 44:48.451
And?

44:48.453 --> 44:53.156
Yeah, and I don't know,
I did something to my back.

44:53.158 --> 44:56.292
When I went to pick it up,
I heard it, so

44:56.294 --> 44:58.795
I rather not make
dinner tonight,

44:58.797 --> 45:00.463
if that's okay with you?

45:00.465 --> 45:03.099
Whatever you want, hon.
I'll bring something home.

45:03.101 --> 45:05.802
Anything in particular?
Oh. You decide.

45:07.272 --> 45:08.371
Bill?

45:09.307 --> 45:11.340
You're feeling okay, right?

45:11.342 --> 45:13.009
Yeah, strong as an ox.

45:13.011 --> 45:14.944
You would tell me
if anything was wrong.

45:14.946 --> 45:16.446
Seriously wrong, right?

45:16.448 --> 45:19.348
Of course.
What's gotten into you?

45:19.350 --> 45:21.451
Oh, nothing. I'm just...

45:21.453 --> 45:23.219
Forget it, I'm just tired.

45:23.221 --> 45:25.755
<i> You go lie down, take it easy,</i>

45:25.757 --> 45:27.924
and I'll be home
before you know it.

45:27.926 --> 45:30.093
Love you.
Love you.

45:56.054 --> 45:57.887
Miss me?

45:57.889 --> 46:00.957
What are you doing here?
You took the words
right out of my mouth.

46:02.393 --> 46:04.243
I'm here to see Philip.

46:04.244 --> 46:06.094
Oh, so you didn't bring
a big fat cheque with you?

46:06.097 --> 46:08.931
The alimony's direct deposit.
I've never missed a payment.

46:08.933 --> 46:11.901
Do you use the same account
to pay Melissa Moody's rent?

46:12.971 --> 46:14.370
Why would you do that?

46:14.372 --> 46:16.239
What else are you
keeping from me, Richard?

46:16.241 --> 46:18.108
Charlene...

46:18.109 --> 46:19.976
You just have this big
web of deceit going on,

46:19.978 --> 46:21.511
and now I have proof.

46:21.513 --> 46:24.013
You son of a bitch!
Okay, I am not
doing this right now.

46:24.015 --> 46:26.349
I can't think of
a better place to do it.
Enough!

46:27.318 --> 46:29.418
I'm here
to see Philip. That's it.

46:29.420 --> 46:32.188
Well, he's on my sofa, so you
might as well get in my car.

46:35.126 --> 46:36.325
(EXHALES)

46:38.797 --> 46:40.429
That false labor again?

46:41.966 --> 46:43.032
Yeah.

46:44.803 --> 46:46.302
What's it feel like?

46:46.304 --> 46:48.504
Feels... tight.

46:48.506 --> 46:51.340
Like everything's clamping up.

46:51.342 --> 46:52.842
Doctor says
I'll know the difference

46:52.844 --> 46:54.844
when it actually happens.

46:54.846 --> 46:56.913
When the baby comes, what then?

46:56.915 --> 46:58.481
Then I'll be a mom.

47:01.986 --> 47:03.553
Best job there is.

47:06.524 --> 47:08.524
Me and Gail
have tried to have kids.

47:09.994 --> 47:13.362
Gail's body just wouldn't take.

47:13.364 --> 47:17.133
We tried a bunch of times, but
she just kept losing them all.

47:17.135 --> 47:19.035
I didn't know that.

47:19.037 --> 47:22.004
I'm sorry.
It made it hard on us,

47:22.006 --> 47:23.606
as a husband and wife...

47:24.542 --> 47:27.009
as a couple.

47:27.011 --> 47:29.278
Ah, it's a beautiful thing,
having kids,

47:29.280 --> 47:30.580
raising them up.

47:30.582 --> 47:32.381
A man has
a lifetime of experience

47:32.383 --> 47:33.549
that he wants to pass down,

47:33.551 --> 47:35.618
something to leave behind.

47:36.888 --> 47:40.590
You know, um,
Gail will never say it, but

47:40.592 --> 47:46.062
she looks at you like
God brought us a little girl

47:46.931 --> 47:48.331
we never had.

48:05.617 --> 48:07.316
Okay. Here...

48:09.053 --> 48:10.653
Where are we?
No, no, no. It's a surprise.

48:10.655 --> 48:12.488
Okay. No peeking.

48:13.658 --> 48:16.158
You sure you don't wanna
go back to prom, and

48:16.160 --> 48:17.660
see the king
and queen announced?

48:17.662 --> 48:19.896
Think I'll live without it.
You want to?

48:19.898 --> 48:21.965
No.

48:21.966 --> 48:24.033
Little further. Little further.
Okay, right here.

48:24.035 --> 48:25.368
RONNIE: One second.

48:25.370 --> 48:26.569
Eyes closed.

48:28.406 --> 48:30.106
Okay, open your eyes.

48:31.910 --> 48:34.443
I still can't see anything.
I know, just one more second.

48:36.648 --> 48:38.214
(ACOUSTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

48:57.335 --> 48:58.634
Okay.
(RONNIE CHUCKLES)

49:01.572 --> 49:03.039
RONNIE: You like it?

49:03.041 --> 49:05.708
Did you do all this?
Phil helped a little.

49:08.079 --> 49:09.178
All right.

50:02.266 --> 50:03.466
I'm ready.

50:04.102 --> 50:05.234
It's perfect.

50:17.181 --> 50:18.280
Gail?

50:29.360 --> 50:30.426
Hon?

50:34.132 --> 50:35.264
Gail?

50:47.445 --> 50:48.511
Gail?

51:38.796 --> 51:41.130
You might wanna slow down.

51:41.131 --> 51:43.465
That's how you wanna start
this conversation? Try again.

51:44.669 --> 51:47.636
Yes, I have been
paying Melissa's rent.

51:47.638 --> 51:49.638
Oh, look at that?
A bit of truth.

51:49.640 --> 51:53.609
So, what makes a grown man pay
the rent of a woman... a girl,

51:53.611 --> 51:55.578
he hasn't seen in five years.

51:59.150 --> 52:00.983
You have seen her.

52:00.984 --> 52:02.817
Holy hell, Richard. You are
a regular bullshit factory!

52:02.820 --> 52:05.888
I come up to the city a couple
of times a year, Charlene.

52:05.890 --> 52:08.858
Barry and I still have
a stake at the medical plaza.

52:08.860 --> 52:10.860
You come in
and you don't call me?

52:10.862 --> 52:13.863
No! No, I don't tell you.

52:14.732 --> 52:16.265
You've made this impossible.

52:16.267 --> 52:18.634
You made it clear
you want nothing to do with me.

52:18.636 --> 52:20.302
Philip's in the city,

52:20.304 --> 52:23.339
and yes, I have seen Melissa.

52:23.341 --> 52:24.607
(TIRES SCREECHING)

52:25.810 --> 52:27.443
(SIGHS)

52:27.445 --> 52:29.678
I knew it.
Oh, calm down, Charlene.

52:29.680 --> 52:32.848
I'm trying to help.
Maybe explain if I could.

52:32.850 --> 52:33.916
Can't wait to hear it.

52:37.522 --> 52:41.323
After Ronnie died, I wanted
to talk about it, Charlene.

52:42.627 --> 52:44.293
I couldn't do that
with you, could I?

52:44.295 --> 52:47.163
You were either curled up
playing dead, or lashing out

52:47.165 --> 52:49.899
and I sure as hell couldn't
lay my grief off onto Philip.

52:51.836 --> 52:53.202
So, everyday...

52:54.472 --> 52:57.339
my bubble just
got a little bit smaller.

52:57.341 --> 52:59.642
And I had no idea
how to make it stop.

53:01.312 --> 53:03.279
One day I was out jogging,

53:04.949 --> 53:07.683
down by the ravine,
not far from where Ronnie died,

53:09.787 --> 53:11.353
I saw her...

53:12.690 --> 53:13.756
Melissa.

53:15.693 --> 53:16.759
And I...

53:18.563 --> 53:20.462
I could have kept going,

53:20.464 --> 53:22.398
let her deal on her own,
but I didn't wanna do that.

53:22.400 --> 53:23.966
I wanted to talk
to her, I want to...

53:25.736 --> 53:28.537
to be with her. And somehow,

53:30.408 --> 53:32.374
I knew she needed me
in the same way.

53:59.437 --> 54:00.703
Shit.

54:08.279 --> 54:09.578
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

54:15.753 --> 54:17.853
MELISSA: Hey.
Hey.

54:17.855 --> 54:19.888
MELISSA: Come in.
Thanks for meeting me.

54:19.890 --> 54:21.824
MELISSA: Oh, no, of course.

54:21.826 --> 54:25.594
I'm really glad you called.
It's nice getting off work
early sometimes.

54:25.596 --> 54:28.797
Sit down. Can I get you
some tea or something?

54:28.799 --> 54:30.299
I just have herbal, but...

54:31.302 --> 54:33.369
No. Thank you though.

54:36.874 --> 54:38.040
Sorry about the...

54:39.310 --> 54:40.409
No.

54:48.019 --> 54:49.385
(EXHALES LOUDLY)

54:50.855 --> 54:52.621
We're quite
the pair, huh? (CHUCKLES)

54:53.024 --> 54:54.390
The blunder twins.

55:09.073 --> 55:10.339
You know, I lied.

55:11.676 --> 55:12.875
Hmm?

55:12.877 --> 55:14.476
About my leg.

55:14.478 --> 55:15.844
It wasn't a bike accident?

55:16.747 --> 55:17.813
It was a bike.

55:21.652 --> 55:22.985
Ronnie and I,

55:23.954 --> 55:25.587
we were supposed
to move to New York.

55:25.589 --> 55:27.022
I remember, yeah.

55:27.024 --> 55:29.425
He talked about it a lot.

55:29.894 --> 55:31.860
So, after...

55:33.331 --> 55:36.365
what happened,
once I was finished with school,

55:36.367 --> 55:39.501
I figured, you know, this is
what Ronnie and I said we'd do.

55:40.404 --> 55:42.004
So, I got a place...

55:43.441 --> 55:46.742
moved to New York. My dad
sent money to cover the rent.

55:48.079 --> 55:50.079
But...

55:50.081 --> 55:52.848
You know, we were supposed
to make it, you know?

55:52.850 --> 55:56.452
On our own,
so in comes the day job.

55:57.388 --> 55:59.521
Bike messenger.
In Manhattan?

55:59.523 --> 56:01.523
In Manhattan.

56:01.525 --> 56:04.526
(SCOFFS) I was actually
pretty good at it,

56:04.528 --> 56:06.495
but at the end
of the day I was alone.

56:07.665 --> 56:11.600
I met people,
but it wasn't the same.

56:13.404 --> 56:15.070
It wasn't what we planned.

56:17.742 --> 56:21.777
So, one day I got a package and
I'm cruising down Fifth Avenue,

56:22.513 --> 56:24.146
and, uh,

56:24.148 --> 56:27.049
in the corner of my eye,
I see this yellow

56:27.918 --> 56:29.051
Honda Prelude

56:30.087 --> 56:32.454
cruising alone,
20-30 miles an hour,

56:33.924 --> 56:35.090
and all I have to do,

56:36.627 --> 56:38.460
is turn the bike
a little to the left,

56:38.462 --> 56:39.762
and I miss him by a mile.

56:43.667 --> 56:44.767
But I don't turn.

56:46.470 --> 56:48.036
You weren't trying to...
No.

56:48.973 --> 56:51.440
No, I wasn't
trying to kill myself.

56:54.578 --> 56:58.046
I guess I just needed
a reason to leave.

57:00.017 --> 57:01.083
You know, to give up,

57:02.887 --> 57:06.522
without giving up.

57:15.032 --> 57:16.465
I should have tried harder

57:17.201 --> 57:18.500
with you.

57:19.904 --> 57:23.038
I know that now.
You left us.

57:23.040 --> 57:25.874
I did. I found a way
to move on, and you hadn't.

57:26.977 --> 57:28.777
I knew I'd fall
right back into it.

57:28.779 --> 57:30.145
So, I got the hell out.

57:31.982 --> 57:33.482
And I know what it did,

57:34.718 --> 57:37.953
to us, to Philip,

57:38.589 --> 57:39.922
we crumbled.

57:39.924 --> 57:41.723
I live with it everyday.

57:41.725 --> 57:43.592
What did you do to her, Richard?

57:47.865 --> 57:50.799
Charlene...
What did you do, Richard?

58:12.890 --> 58:14.523
Thank you

58:15.626 --> 58:16.925
for trusting me.

58:18.562 --> 58:20.762
The fact still remains I quit.

58:20.764 --> 58:23.765
I took a way out, but...

58:25.870 --> 58:27.236
God, here you are!

58:28.672 --> 58:30.272
As big as a house...
(CHUCKLES)

58:30.274 --> 58:33.041
...on the edge
of this giant step, and

58:33.043 --> 58:35.777
you still have the guts
to go toe-to-toe with my mother.

58:36.914 --> 58:38.547
And the whole goddamn town.

58:39.283 --> 58:40.716
You didn't quit.

58:42.052 --> 58:43.952
And I want you know
that you're not alone.

58:45.956 --> 58:49.558
I might not believe
that this is Ronnie's baby,

58:51.128 --> 58:53.829
but I believe
that you believe it.

58:53.831 --> 58:57.065
And I believe that Ronnie
would have believed it too.

58:58.035 --> 58:59.134
So,

59:00.771 --> 59:02.571
if that makes me an uncle,

59:04.675 --> 59:05.908
so be it.

59:09.313 --> 59:10.746
I mean,

59:12.850 --> 59:13.982
it's not like...

59:14.885 --> 59:18.053
it's not like I'm so sure, 24/7.

59:21.191 --> 59:24.192
Some days it's hard enough just

59:24.962 --> 59:26.094
waking up.

59:27.164 --> 59:30.699
Some days I wake up, and

59:31.902 --> 59:33.802
I don't remember
much of anything.

59:39.743 --> 59:43.779
MELISSA:<i> I pass out,</i>
<i> and I dream about Ronnie.</i>

59:45.182 --> 59:46.748
<i> And the night we made love.</i>

59:48.986 --> 59:52.621
<i> But, when I come</i>
<i> to the next morning,</i>

59:54.725 --> 59:57.359
<i> everything just feels off.</i>

59:59.163 --> 1:00:01.163
<i> It feels different.</i>

1:00:03.267 --> 1:00:04.733
So, I make mistakes,

1:00:06.036 --> 1:00:08.103
I get confused,

1:00:08.105 --> 1:00:10.906
Join the club.
And I know...

1:00:11.942 --> 1:00:13.809
I know everybody talks about me.

1:00:14.912 --> 1:00:18.947
The psycho
pregnant girl with the

1:00:19.850 --> 1:00:21.116
dead boyfriend.

1:00:22.353 --> 1:00:23.719
But...

1:00:26.624 --> 1:00:28.924
But it's okay.

1:00:28.926 --> 1:00:32.327
BILL: Gail? Can you
come down here for a sec?

1:00:34.398 --> 1:00:36.331
CHARLENE:<i> What</i>
<i> did you do to her?</i>

1:00:36.333 --> 1:00:38.767
Nothing. At first,
we just talked...

1:00:40.170 --> 1:00:41.670
About Ronnie,

1:00:41.672 --> 1:00:44.239
and that silly accent
he used to do.

1:00:44.241 --> 1:00:46.241
His clothes, anything.

1:00:47.378 --> 1:00:49.011
After a while,

1:00:49.013 --> 1:00:52.381
we filled in the gaps where
our normal lives fell apart.

1:00:53.884 --> 1:00:56.952
Melissa's parents found out.
They didn't approve.

1:00:56.954 --> 1:00:58.920
I guess it got heated
and she moved out,

1:00:58.922 --> 1:01:00.689
and I felt like I
owed it to Ronnie to

1:01:01.258 --> 1:01:03.025
take care of her.

1:01:03.027 --> 1:01:05.360
Got her a place, paid the rent,

1:01:06.830 --> 1:01:09.064
gave her some
spare cash the first year.

1:01:10.968 --> 1:01:12.167
And the next.

1:01:15.439 --> 1:01:18.240
After a while,
it just became a habit.

1:01:19.376 --> 1:01:21.443
Like anything else.

1:01:21.445 --> 1:01:23.011
So, you didn't sleep with her?

1:01:24.448 --> 1:01:26.748
Christ! No, Charlene.

1:01:28.385 --> 1:01:29.951
Of course not.

1:01:31.855 --> 1:01:32.988
Who would do that?

1:01:33.957 --> 1:01:35.257
It's like I'm trying
to find my way out

1:01:35.259 --> 1:01:36.858
of one of those corn mazes

1:01:36.860 --> 1:01:38.326
that they put up
at Thanksgiving,

1:01:39.797 --> 1:01:43.799
and I'm going down a different
path than everyone else.

1:01:45.769 --> 1:01:47.369
But I know it's the right one.

1:01:51.041 --> 1:01:52.174
<i> Meanwhile, everyone else is</i>

1:01:52.176 --> 1:01:54.342
going down their
own paths thinking about

1:01:55.179 --> 1:01:56.878
how wrong everyone else is.

1:01:59.283 --> 1:02:03.218
But, I figure if I go my way,

1:02:05.322 --> 1:02:06.922
and you go yours,

1:02:11.361 --> 1:02:13.762
<i> we're all gonna wind up</i>
<i> in the same place at the end.</i>

1:02:20.337 --> 1:02:21.937
(STUTTERS) I wanna apologize.

1:02:24.842 --> 1:02:26.174
For what?

1:02:26.176 --> 1:02:27.342
For the cigarettes.

1:02:28.946 --> 1:02:30.779
I see you found 'em.

1:02:30.781 --> 1:02:34.282
That's an old stash, before our
conversation the other night.

1:02:34.284 --> 1:02:37.185
That's all right, Bill.
I understand.

1:02:37.187 --> 1:02:40.122
It's over now, I swear it.

1:02:42.259 --> 1:02:43.325
Forgive me?

1:02:50.534 --> 1:02:52.534
I went to the pharmacy

1:02:52.536 --> 1:02:56.371
to find out what they were
because I thought you were sick.

1:02:56.373 --> 1:03:00.075
You... you son of a bitch!

1:03:00.077 --> 1:03:01.877
Now wait a minute,
let's not get unhinged.

1:03:01.879 --> 1:03:04.546
How should I react? You tell me!

1:03:04.548 --> 1:03:06.381
It's not like that.

1:03:06.383 --> 1:03:09.351
God! 30 years!

1:03:10.087 --> 1:03:12.053
Under the same roof.

1:03:12.956 --> 1:03:16.892
The whole time, I was the idiot!

1:03:16.894 --> 1:03:18.960
I don't know what it is
you think you know.

