Driver, the lovers
have arrived. Onwards!

1:14:45.582 --> 1:14:46.881
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

1:15:01.931 --> 1:15:04.765
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1:15:10.840 --> 1:15:13.207
Philip!

1:15:38.301 --> 1:15:39.700
(PHONE BEEPS)

1:15:42.005 --> 1:15:43.671
It's not connecting.

1:15:43.673 --> 1:15:46.641
Reception's bad out here.
He's in trouble.

1:15:47.110 --> 1:15:48.609
I heard it in his voice.

1:15:48.611 --> 1:15:50.044
It's the baby, she due.

1:15:50.046 --> 1:15:52.179
Well, then why doesn't
he pick up his phone?

1:15:52.181 --> 1:15:54.515
He's driving.

1:15:54.516 --> 1:15:56.850
He doesn't wanna talk
on the phone. He's a smart kid.

1:16:04.861 --> 1:16:05.927
Hey.

1:16:07.263 --> 1:16:09.096
We'll find him.

1:16:09.098 --> 1:16:12.667
You remember
when Ronnie was born?
Of course.

1:16:13.336 --> 1:16:15.202
God, that labor was so painful.

1:16:17.006 --> 1:16:18.839
Screaming my head off.

1:16:21.611 --> 1:16:24.612
But then when the doctor put his
little body right on my chest,

1:16:24.614 --> 1:16:26.347
I just started laughing.

1:16:28.952 --> 1:16:30.284
Do you remember?

1:16:31.721 --> 1:16:34.288
Yeah.
He was so happy.

1:16:39.162 --> 1:16:40.995
I think about that a lot.

1:16:47.670 --> 1:16:48.936
Richard,

1:16:49.739 --> 1:16:51.005
the gate.

1:17:30.346 --> 1:17:31.679
Hello?

1:17:33.383 --> 1:17:34.782
Hello?

1:17:38.421 --> 1:17:41.288
Forget it, nobody's here.
Come on.
No, no. Let's look around.

1:17:43.960 --> 1:17:45.292
Dr. Chase.

1:17:46.029 --> 1:17:47.895
Nice to see you again.

1:17:47.897 --> 1:17:52.299
Hey, Bill. Yeah, I moved
my trip up a couple of days.

1:17:52.301 --> 1:17:54.368
Um, sorry to bother you,

1:17:54.370 --> 1:17:58.072
this is a little odd. We're
looking for our son Philip.

1:17:58.074 --> 1:18:00.274
He's 21, brown hair.
He's on crutches.

1:18:00.276 --> 1:18:03.444
We got a call from him. He was
gonna meet up with Melissa,

1:18:03.446 --> 1:18:06.147
but nobody's at the house. So...

1:18:06.149 --> 1:18:09.350
I've been here for a bit,
and I haven't seen anyone.

1:18:11.287 --> 1:18:13.287
You don't think
the baby's come? Do you?

1:18:13.289 --> 1:18:16.090
I think that's a real
possibility, yes.

1:18:16.092 --> 1:18:19.126
It's probably where he is,
down at the hospital.

1:18:19.128 --> 1:18:21.162
You should check it out.

1:18:21.164 --> 1:18:24.098
Gail's gone down
to the store for some food.

1:18:24.100 --> 1:18:26.367
As soon as she's back,
we'll be on your tail.

1:18:27.270 --> 1:18:29.036
Okay. Okay, good.

1:18:29.038 --> 1:18:31.138
Sorry to bother you,
we'll see you at the hospital.

1:18:32.375 --> 1:18:34.408
You head. What happened?

1:18:35.111 --> 1:18:36.177
Uh...

1:18:37.814 --> 1:18:39.847
Number one rule in carpentry,

1:18:40.717 --> 1:18:42.383
don't daydream.

1:18:42.385 --> 1:18:45.319
I should take a look at that.
Oh, no, it's nothing.
It's just a cut.

1:18:46.489 --> 1:18:48.422
Nothing I haven't
done a thousand times.

1:18:48.424 --> 1:18:50.224
(CHUCKLES)

1:18:50.226 --> 1:18:52.960
So, I'll see you
down at maternity.

1:18:55.798 --> 1:18:56.897
Okay.

1:19:05.441 --> 1:19:06.907
Something's not right.

1:19:06.909 --> 1:19:09.176
Charlene, you don't
know that, all right.

1:19:09.178 --> 1:19:11.278
We're gonna go
to the hospital...
Why the hell are you so calm?

1:19:11.280 --> 1:19:13.314
Because I'm not
jumping to conclusions.

1:19:13.316 --> 1:19:15.416
You didn't hear him,
Richard, he's in trouble.

1:19:15.418 --> 1:19:17.318
We will find him.

1:19:17.319 --> 1:19:19.219
You didn't hear him, Richard.
He's not safe!

1:19:20.957 --> 1:19:22.256
(CRYING)

1:19:26.395 --> 1:19:29.163
Richard...
Okay, Charlene.

1:19:29.165 --> 1:19:30.498
Richard.

1:20:01.197 --> 1:20:03.230
Whoa, whoa, whoa, okay,
somebody get me a wheelchair.

1:20:03.800 --> 1:20:05.466
Wheelchair, now.

1:20:05.468 --> 1:20:08.502
Okay, okay. Put her in there.
Okay, breathe.

1:20:08.504 --> 1:20:10.337
Easy does it. There you go.

1:20:11.307 --> 1:20:13.274
Okay. How far apart
are your contractions?

1:20:15.344 --> 1:20:16.977
I don't know, a minute.

1:20:16.979 --> 1:20:19.446
Okay, is there
someone we can call?

1:20:19.448 --> 1:20:21.582
Gail Herman...
Can you tell me
your name please?

1:20:31.494 --> 1:20:32.993
(GLASS BREAKING)

1:20:38.367 --> 1:20:39.433
Wait here.

1:20:40.269 --> 1:20:41.502
Please.

1:21:45.601 --> 1:21:47.001
Where are you?

1:21:49.338 --> 1:21:50.471
Where are you?

1:22:41.157 --> 1:22:42.256
Jesus.

1:22:47.563 --> 1:22:48.729
Richard.

1:22:50.099 --> 1:22:51.999
She's dead.

1:22:52.001 --> 1:22:54.068
Snapped her neck.
Oh, my God.

1:22:54.070 --> 1:22:57.171
Outside. Outside. Call 911.

1:22:57.173 --> 1:22:59.473
CHARLENE: I'm not
getting a signal.
RICHARD: Try again.

1:22:59.475 --> 1:23:01.408
We have to find Philip.
He's not in the house.

